name: dl-pin-2(3)-ene
Reason: 1,2-dichloroethene has a melting point of -109.4 degrees Celsius. The introduction of two fluorine substituents increases the melting point due to strong electronegativity which leads to stronger intermolecular dipole-dipole interactions. Each fluorine is estimated to increase the melting point by approximately 15 degrees Celsius, giving a total increase of (15 degrees Celsius x 2 fluorines) = 30 degrees Celsius.
